==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in the late 15th century.
* {{suffix|accumulate|tion|lang=en}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ə.ˌkjum.jə.ˈle.ʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-accumulation.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of amassing or gathering, as into a pile.
# The process of growing into a heap or a large amount.
#: ''an '''accumulation''' of earth, of sand, of evils, of wealth, or of honors''
# A mass of something piled up or collected.
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} The [[concurrence]] of several titles to the same proof.
# {{context|accounting|lang=en}} The continuous growth of [[capital]] by [[retention]] of [[interest]] or [[savings]].
# {{context|finance|lang=en}} The action of investors buying an [[asset]] from other [[investor]]s when the [[price]] of the asset is low.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|accounting}} [[retained earnings]]

====Antonyms====
* [[decumulation]]

